1. Hook into Foundry VTT's 'canvasReady' event
2. Check if a cached navmesh exists in scene flags using `scene.getFlag('routinglib', 'navmeshData')`
3. If no cache exists, instantiate the NavmeshBuilder class
4. Generate the navmesh using wall data from `canvas.walls.documents` and dimensions from `canvas.dimensions`
5. Filter out open doors (where `wall.ds === 2`)
6. Implement proper error handling for failed navmesh generation

Code structure:
```javascript
Hooks.on('canvasReady', async (canvas) => {
  const scene = game.scenes.current;
  const cachedNavmesh = scene.getFlag('routinglib', 'navmeshData');

  if (cachedNavmesh) {
    // Load from cache
    loadNavmeshFromCache(cachedNavmesh);
    return;
  }

  // Generate new navmesh
  try {
    const walls = canvas.walls.documents.filter(w => w.ds !== 2); // Filter out open doors
    const navmeshBuilder = new NavmeshBuilder();
    const navmeshData = await navmeshBuilder.buildNavmesh(walls, canvas.dimensions);

    // Cache the result
    await scene.setFlag('routinglib', 'navmeshData', navmeshData);

    // Initialize pathfinding with the new navmesh
    initializePathfinding(navmeshData);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Failed to generate navmesh:', error);
    // Implement fallback strategy
  }
});
